# 🔍 PORT-SCAN

A browser-based network reconnaissance tool that demonstrates TCP handshake mechanics, service detection, and port scanning methodology.

## 🚀 Live Demo

https://adamanuhu-star.github.io/port-scan

## 📊 Features

- **Port Range Selection** — Common ports, web services, remote access, databases, or full range
- **Scan Types** — SYN Stealth, TCP Connect, UDP scanning simulation
- **Real-time Visualization** — Port grid lights up as scan progresses
- **Service Fingerprinting** — Banner grabbing, version detection, OS guessing
- **Risk Assessment** — Identifies high-risk exposed services
- **Security Recommendations** — Hardening advice based on findings

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- HTML5, Tailwind CSS, Vanilla JavaScript
- No external dependencies
- Simulated scanning environment for educational purposes

## 🎯 Networking Concepts Demonstrated

- **TCP Handshake:** SYN, SYN-ACK, ACK states and port states (open/closed/filtered)
- **Service Detection:** Banner grabbing and version fingerprinting
- **OS Fingerprinting:** Inferring operating system from open port patterns
- **Network Security:** Identifying exposed services and attack surface

